HTML(Hypertext Markup Language) - a markup language
HTML Elements - to write HTML, we pick from a set of standar elements that all browers recognize
  i.e.  <p> elements
        <h1> element
        <img> element
        <form> element
  -consists of a opening tag <p> and a closing tag </p>
HTML Skeleton
  -We write our HTML in a standard 'Skeleton' aka 'Boilerplate'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
    <title>My First Page</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- Content Goes Here -->
  </body>
  </html>

<html> element
  -contains one head element and one body element
  -has all the meta data meaning it does not show up in the document itself
<head> element 
  -contains machine-readable metadata(information) about the document
  <title> element
    -defines the title of the document for the browser tab
<body> element>
  -contains the entire content of the page

***TIPS***
-typing ! + tab will give boilerplayer in a html doc
-format document will format the html
-ctrl + alt + down/up will duplicate line up/down

List Elements
ol- order list of items numbered
ul- unordered list of items bullet points
li- list items and must have a ol/ul parent

<a>- Anchor Tags - used to create hyperlinks
  must use a href="<link>"